An overall recount can also be carried out if, after a proper count, it is found that the difference between the likely winner and the candidate in second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, and also whenever there is an explicit request from a political party whose candidate has finished second. In this case, electoral packages for which a partial census has been carried out will be excluded.
