Yesterday's meeting in Sant Andreu was attended by a large number of representatives of organisations and institutions that have worked with the association over the past 25 years.
The diverse political representation, at the time of the elections, showed the uniform nature of the work carried out by Trinijove.
Together with The Generalitat President, Arthur Mas, and his predecessor, Jordi Pujol, the ceremony was attended by former Socialist Education Advisor Ernest Maragall, and former Deputy Mayor and current Environmental Socialist Councillor Ricard Goma.
The current Social Welfare and Family Advisor, Josep Lluís Cleries, and the Director General of Social Work at La Caixa, Jaume Lanaspa, also appeared at the large Fabra i Coats Hall.
